<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I think that's a neat idea...but honestly, I don't think it'll fly.  Setting up a message system like that would be easy enough for the programmers to implement, however, when you take into consideration the sheer number of people that will be playing, an option like that would require an enormous amount of server space.  Plus...it would be just one more thing that people could complain to the GMs about..."Why didn't I get this message?  You guys suck..you can't even keep a message system going!"  It really seems as though people are never satisfied with anything that they try to do...so why bother?<P>Additionally...if you would like to get offline messages...I would recommend using Email directly.  I set up a Hotmail account specifically for gaming.  It's free...and it's effective.<P>IMHO, the /tell system will work more than great for ingame purposes...if you want to send someone a message offline, use Email.<P>--------------------<P> <IMG SRC="http://www.geocities.com/ak_empire/images/AKE_LOGO1Anim.gif"> <P>The New Empire has risen!<BR>Join the <A HREF="http://www.geocities.com/ak_empire/" TARGET=_blank>Abyssal Knight Empire</A> or parrish in our wake!
